  <span id="freeText10882483578579092442" style="display:none">The quintessential road trip across America, this one dedicated to PIE - berry, icebox, custard and cream. Kind of like Thelma and Louise but not as crazy. Kind of like Miles and Jake, but not as disaffected. Nice insights into vanishing America, the art and craft of pie disappearing with the death of the diner, the loss of the last generation but hope in odd places like Pie Town New Mexico, Georgia and Michigan. The aimless trip through upstate New York and New England, when Pascale and boyfriend inserted themselves into someone else's Thanksgiving dinner was certainly odd. Lots of unusual pies and recipes.</span>
