  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2241141054" />
    <a title="Kirsten" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/922950-kirsten"><img alt="Kirsten" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1467306276p2/922950.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2241141054?book_show_action=true">Jan 19, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kirsten" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kirsten" href="/user/show/922950-kirsten">Kirsten</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2241141054" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15783320952232443739">I loved this book of stories about a road trip looking for pie, but I think you have to be in the mood for it. I loved the lessons she learned on the way. And now all I want to do is master the art of pie crust so I can bake every pie recipe from the book.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


